<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>i</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mi>D</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msub><m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontstyle="italic"><m:mrow><m:mtext>ref</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ \( i rSub { size 8{D} }  \)  rSub { size 8{ ital "ref"} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> would be coupled with a compensating adjustment in 
